<node><name>Do a Mini-Presentation</name>
<id>5</id>
<lefticon>class</lefticon>
<righticon>discuss</righticon>
<column>ICS</column>
<textHTML>&lt;p&gt;Each interview pair presents each other to the class in a one-minute analysis according to the template:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is [name] who says that if they were a [category], they would be [response].&amp;nbsp;This indicates/suggests they&amp;nbsp;[analysis of connotations]&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note:&amp;nbsp;Be careful not to make literal interpretations, i.e. “They said if they were a beverage, they would be lemonade which means they like lemonade.”&amp;nbsp;What does lemonade connote?&amp;nbsp;“They said if they were a beverage, they would be lemonade which suggests they are a refreshing, light person who you want to be around; someone who lifts people up and makes them feel happy.”&lt;/p&gt;</textHTML>
